B.anO=new A.dg("What is the Reads tab?","Reads is your private database of opponent notes. Add any player you've encountered and record tells, tendencies, bet-sizing patterns, or any observations from your time at the table with them.")
B.aoc=new A.dg("How do I add a read?","Go to the Reads tab and tap the + button. Enter the player's name and your notes. You can add and edit notes over time as you encounter the player in future sessions.")
B.aoe=new A.dg("Can I use Reads with the Hand Recorder?","Yes. When recording a hand, player name fields autocomplete from your Reads database. This lets you build a connected record of hands involving players you've profiled.")
B.ao3=new A.dg("Can I share a player read?","Yes. Open a read's detail view and tap the share icon. This exports the player name and your notes as plain text to share via any app.")
